sed_at": "2017-08-23T19:07:17Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "\r\n```shell\r\nhopa:/tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData\r\n$> datalad install Utah_1\r\nget(notneeded): /tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData/Utah_1 (dataset) [already installed]\r\n2 19974.....................................:Wed 14 Jun 2017 03:45:33 PM EDT:.\r\nhopa:/tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData\r\n$> datalad uninstall Utah_1\r\nuninstall(error): /tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData/Utah_1 (dataset) [will not uninstall top-level dataset (consider `remove` command)]\r\n2 19975 ->1.....................................:Wed 14 Jun 2017 03:45:36 PM EDT:.\r\nhopa:/tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData\r\n$> datalad uninstall -d . Utah_1\r\ndrop(notneeded): Utah_1 (directory) [nothing to drop from /tmp/datasets.datalad.org/corr/RawData/Utah_1]\r\nuninstall(ok): Utah_1 (dataset)\r\naction summary:\r\n  drop (notneeded: 1)\r\n  uninstall (ok: 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIMHO more logical to have symmetric api here and be able to uninstall what we install with similar invocation.\r\n\r\nMoreover I thought that `remove` should actually remove (`git rm`) upon completing drop/uninstall... otherwise I am  really not clear on their difference(s)", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.